THE group of men armed who attacked a cash truck in Ngaleni,
in Port St John have been arrested. The thugs used explosives
to open the cash van and made off with an undisclosed amount of money. Cops were informed that the thugs were driving towards Gauteng. On the N1 highway outside Sasolburg, the suspects were
arrested driving in a hired silver Toyota Etios. Cops found the money stolen from the cash van heist hidden
inside the door panels. The four suspects were then arrested on the scene. “Money was removed from the panels and counted on the scene.
Some of the notes were damaged and we suspect were damaged by explosion during
robbery,” the cops said. 